A 28-year-old woman, Abigail Agbubla Tetteh, has been arrested by the police in Tema New Town, Ghana, for allegedly poisoning her two children to death. http://instablog9ja.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/instablog9ja_20200801_13.mp4 <img src="https://i1.wp.com/instablog9ja.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/instablog9ja_20200801_14.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024" /> The children, a boy and a girl aged two and eight months respectively, were killed with rat poison on Wednesday night, July 29, 2020. They were found dead on a bed and locked up in their rooms, on Thursday, after residents became suspicious of their whereabouts. The suspect initially fled the scene but was arrested by some residents who handed her to the police. Upon interrogation, Abigail said she committed the hideous crime because she could no longer afford to take care of them. [Swipe] Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.